definitions.definition: ( slang , chiefly Australia , New Zealand ) To report (a person) to someone in authority for a wrongdoing .
( slang , chiefly Australia ) To do one's share; to contribute.
examples: We all dobbed in for a gift when he retired.

definitions.definition: ( slang , chiefly Australia ) To nominate a person, often in their absence, for an unpleasant task.
( slang , Northern Ireland ) To play truant

main_definition: ( slang , chiefly Australia , New Zealand ) To report (a person) to someone in authority for a wrongdoing .

definitions.definition: In the scouting movement, to chant dob to indicate that one will do one's best to follow the scouting laws.

main_definition: ( intransitive , sometimes humorous ) In the scouting movement, to chant dob to indicate that one will do one's best to follow the scouting laws.
